        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 9:23PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 923 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fluvanna, or 12 miles southwest of Lake Alan Henry, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fluvanna.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
